SIX is a gamble. I can share a little history FYI.

Maybe the preferred stock is less a gamble than the common. (PKS previous stock
symbol) The preferred stock was recommended on the value website and maybe
discussed here years ago. The preferred B shares are mandatory redeemable at
$25 (cash or stock) on 2/15/2009. The stock is presently at $21.45 and pays
$1.81 div per year (8.4%) add the appreciation if/when redeemed and you get a
yield of over 15%. Back in 2003, when first mentioned, the pref stock was at
$17, and the yield was even higher. I sold the last of my pref shares just last
week to add to various energy investments.

