Date:9/17/2006 5:33:35 AM
From:John Carragher
ot
hope you signed up for two year contract to hold your monthly price for at
least two years. friend of mine signed up one year and a few months back got a
price increase. not much a few dollars.

there is big difference between cable and optic. with vz you have your own
direct line on a fiber smaller than a hair. on cable you share the line with
the community. as more and more of your neighbors get on their pc your response
time slows down as you are all sharing the same line.

cable is more un-relieable imo it is laid about six inches under the ground and
every tom , dick and harry who works in his yard or has a contractor come
through cuts the line. also the lines outside developments run along the
telephone poles and usually every wind storm the cable goes out or quality of
delivery gets real bad. Also it seems cable has more connections to maintain in
these control boxes outside your house or along the lines. It seems comcast is
always working the lines or boxes. i have never had an interruption in my optic
since installation vs my neighbor across from me has lost service several
times. after a year now he is convinced the price of cable is lower but not
worth it.

next will be optic delivery tv. presently in some states and calf is now
looking at giving approval state wide vs having to negotiate approval in each
community.

