Hi John/Paul

I hope you don't mind if I throw in a couple of my thoughts on your
conversation. I think Verizon is way ahead of most other companies because of
their decision to commit so heavily to true fiber-to-the-home. The argument
against FTTH has always been cost for connecting the last mile. Japan FTTH has
exploded and it has proven to be very successful. New technologies are and will
continue to increase the capacity of fiber at a magnitude greater then cable.
The services that Verizon will be able to deliver and the ultimate cost savings
of fiber will pay off in the long run. As well deployment methods are helping
to dramatically drop the cost of fiber to the premises. So the $20 billion or
so that Verizon is proposing to spend on FTTH should be an extremely wise
investment in securing dominance.

