of 2006 from year-end 2005 levels. While there was growth in all vessel
categories, the highest percentage increase occurred in the Panamax sector,
where tonnage increased by 8.0% since the beginning of the year. VLCCs, on the
other hand, experienced the lowest percentage growth at 1.8%. This additional
tonnage exerted downward pressure on TCE rates and is a key factor as to why
rates during the first half of 2006 were lower than 2005 in all vessel
categories except VLCCs."

